<subSubSection id="19E947A9BB36E1F6809EF252CDA1E31A" pageId="18" pageNumber="67" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="11F6A5D606527CE118D7A075DEBE4F94" pageId="18" pageNumber="67">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B0C54C2691D8D32289F8AF5756703C47" pageId="18" pageNumber="67">
Fifty five of the 58 species of the genus are Nearctic. All species of 
<taxonomicName id="C2A1D047EDFEA648EA8AAA4A67AB7C46" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Paravilla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Paravilla" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Paravilla</taxonomicName>
collected in Coahuila were exclusively collected in the summer months from April to July. 
<bibRefCitation id="E5B225984AD0C263A9AF3B7CD74DEC27" author="Hall, JC" journalOrPublisher="University of California Publications in Entomology" pageId="29" pageNumber="78" pagination="1 - 190" title="A review of the North and Central American species of Paravilla Painter (Diptera: Bombyliidae)." volume="92" year="1981 a">Hall (1981a)</bibRefCitation>
reviewed this genus and presented a key for species and description of new species.
</paragraph>
